tspan.tspan: 1. In Initiative Order Players Declare War and change
Military Doctrines.
a. Declare War – Against any Player or Principality
unless already Declare on.
i. Foreign Powers may not Declare or be Declare on
unless they have provinces of allies in the Empire.
b. Declare Religious War – Team War. Max 1/Round.
Resolved Next Phase.
i. Only Saved Players may Declare. Become ROTF.
ii. May only Declare against potential Target
Principalities.
c. Change Military Doctrine – Simply move your cube.
2. Battles & Peace Treaties in Battle Phase Order
a. Battles
i. If you have 2x Imperial power as opponent, auto-
win.
ii. Unaligned Principalities have 2x Imperial Power
than as an ally
iii. Draw 1 Card/IP, up to 12. Place Reserve Token for
extra IP
iv. Perform Military Doctrine. May trade Gold for extra
cards 1:1
b. Peace Treaties – If you win, you can:
i. Conquer 1 province with a town. Lose 3 DI; or
ii. Vassalize a town; or
iii. Conquer 2 non-town provinces. Lose 1 DI for every
non-adjacent province.
iv. Allies may take 1 adjacent non-town province. Lose
2 DI if can but don’t.
v. If you lose, you lose 2 DI with each of your allies per
province they lose.
